org.wtc.eclipse.platform.helpers
Interface IJavaDebuggingHelper

public interface IJavaDebuggingHelper

Helper for interacting with the views in the debug perspective and for verifying debugging operations are executed as expected with a currently running process (In other words, if a test is testing that a breakpoint will be hit in an application deployed to a server, it is the responsibility of the caller to start that server in debug mode.

setLineBreakpoint

void setLineBreakpoint(IUIContext ui,
                       IPath filePath,
                       int breakpointLine)
setLineBreakpoint - Add a breakpoint to the given file on the given line.

Parameters:
ui - - Driver for UI generated input
filePath - - The full path (project included) of the file in which to set a breakpoint.
breakpointLine - - The line number (Eclipse files start numbering files with line number 1) on which to set a breakpoint. If the given line number is greater than the line length of the given file, this method will issue a test case failure. Note that if the line number is placed on a non-executable line (in a Java comment or on a line with a brace ('{') for a conditional statement, the breakpoint may not be set or may jump to the nearest possible executable line depending on internal Eclipse breakpoint processing and this method will issue a test case failure

setMethodBreakpoint - Locate the first occurrence of the method with the given signature search parameters, and toggle a method breakpoint on that method.

Parameters:
ui - - Driver for UI generated input
filePath - - The full path (project included) of the file in which to set a breakpoint. Must be a Java file
typeName - - The short name of the enclosing type of the method that will have a breakpoint set
methodName - - The name of the method that is to have a breakpoint set
methodReturnType - - The return type (or "void") that appears on the method signature whose breakpoint should be set

verifySuspendedAtLine - Wait until a debugged process exists and is suspended at the given line in the given file. It is the responsibility of the caller to begin a process in debug mode, and to resume a suspended process.
